reviews.review_text: Any Show at the Greek is Hot The boys were kicking some ass The  night before with the pull out of Dark star was hot The boys were on a roll Listen to Big railroad blues jerry is so on    ya

Great Shows I remember these shows as extremely HOT. The crowd was salavating as the boys just kept pulling out the rawest yet most synchronized versions of songs that bridge the mid-to mid-late stages--a particularly ripe time. Jerry had something to prove with these shows--seriously! He is on fire--shredding every possible chord on even the early songs--blistering from the start!!! And then there is Brent, who I think had found just the right mixture of everything on these....What do you do the day after a third set Dark Star? Listen and find out...
Totaly bitchen show! very nice recording with non stop action.This is a keeper
Franklin's I am live in western ny and the franklin's was added to my syracuse ny show.  It is  one of the best franklin's I have ever heard.
re: Franklin's Uh, yeah, dude, that Franklin's is insane!
WOW!!!! Too cool. I really liked the Jack Straw,Big Railroad Blues. It was real livly sounding.And the sound quality is Saaaaweeeet with a capital S. Really long jams on this one.
roooster who's doing the killer harmonica on rooster?  its spot on!  and i dont usually go for rooster!

Best ever! The Help>Slip>Franklins>, and really the whole second set if stellar!  This was the original show that was given to me on cassette back in the day that turned me on to these guys. I only had the second set back then; thanks to archive.org and Charlie Miller, I now have the whole show. This is the GD at their best in front of a home audience. Jerry's tone is magical!
Harmonica Player Matthew Kelly is on the harmonica during Rooster

My FIRST SHOW Thank you for helping me remember and listen to my very first Grateful Dead show 33 years ago today.  What a long strange trip it's been. Some of these songs heard at my first show remain my favorites. I was at Fenway in June to see Dead & Company. ..cms
Space Very solid 84’ Dead. I found the space on this concert to be very pleasing to the ears!

Dayum!!! Another amazing mid 80's show! I've had an audience recording on a Maxwell for years and have loved it. I KNEW how good of a show this was before ever hearing this pristine version, but this.....this blew my hair back. Thank you fellas! Thank you Charlie! Total love ❤️ ⚡️💙
